cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.DC 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it discusses the use of programmable switches for network measurement tasks. It may also belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as network measurement tasks can be used for security purposes. Additionally, it could be classified under the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Programming Languages (cs.PL) as it proposes a new approach to composing measurement tasks using reusable building blocks. Finally, it could be classified under the sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as network measurement tasks often involve distributed systems.
